sparql_query_kg2:
 Based on the provided context and the mappings between Wikidata and DBpedia, here is the SPARQL query for DBpedia to retrieve all swimmers that were born in Moscow:

```sparql
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX res: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri rdf:type dbo:Swimmer ;
        dbo:birthPlace res:Moscow .
}
```

This query uses the DBpedia ontology and resource identifiers as specified in the entity and relation mapping (ER2).

